;; KNOWN ISSUE — qlot install does NOT follow package-inferred-system
;; deps. jsonrpc/transport/tcp uses :import-from #:cl+ssl etc., which
;; aren't visible to qlot's installer. A fresh `qlot install` here
;; will leave the swank-lsp suite unable to load (cl+ssl, fast-io,
;; flexi-streams, static-vectors, lw-compat, ... all missing).
;;
;; Workaround for a fresh checkout: either (a) `qlot add` each missing
;; transitive dep until it loads, or (b) wrap the entrypoint in
;; `ql:quickload :swank-lsp` before `asdf:load-system`, since
;; quickload has lazy resolution. The previous (working) .qlot/
;; directory was built up incrementally over Phase 1+2 dev and
;; couldn't be reproduced from this qlfile alone.
;;
;; This is a pre-existing qlot limitation, not a regression from the
;; cl-scope-resolver split.
